System Design Interview: TV Channel Subscription
System Problem Statement:
Design a subscription management system for a streaming TV platform.

Requirements:

Multi-pack Channels: A channel can belong to multiple packages
(e.g., ESPN in both "Sports Pack" and "Premium Bundle")

Package Subscriptions: Users can subscribe to packages with auto-renewal:

Billing cycles: Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly

Auto-renews unless cancelled

Pay-Per-Day Channels: Users can buy individual channels:
Each channel has a daily price User pays upfront:
Daily Price × Number of Days No auto-renewal, expires after purchased duration
Example: ESPN ₹10/day for 15 days = ₹150 upfront

Graceful Cancellation: Cancelled subscriptions remain active until the paid period ends 1.
--------------------------------
Data Model & Entities Design core entities: Channel, Package, User, PackageSubscription, ChannelPurchase
Show relationships (ER diagram or table schemas) Include key attributes, data types, primary/foreign keys

How do you track subscription states and validity periods?
What indexes are needed for performance?
--------------------------------
2. REST API Design Design user-facing APIs (no admin APIs):

Subscribe to package
Cancel subscription
Purchase channel for N days
Get my active subscriptions/purchases
Check channel access (entitlement)
----------------------------------
3. High-Level Design Micro services architecture
(User, Subscription, Channel Purchase, Entitlement, Payment, Notification services)
Show interaction flows for: Package subscription Channel purchase
Entitlement check (real-time, <100ms) Auto-renewal job

Database choices and caching strategy Sequence diagrams for critical flows